definition: on top/upon/above/upper/previous/first (of multiple parts)/to climb/to get onto/to go up/to attend (class or university)

sentences.english: Enter the recently named Vice President, Lieut.
sentences.chinese: 輸入最近任命爲副總裁，上尉。

sentences.english: Captain Aoyagi, the company commander, was killed while he directed the defense.
sentences.chinese: 連隊指揮官，青柳上尉，在直接參加防禦戰時陣亡。

sentences.english: A captain in the Navy ranks above a captain in the Army.
sentences.chinese: 美國陸軍上尉或海軍上校有由總統簽名的委任狀。

sentences.english: Ahsoka raised her head and found herself looking at Capitan Rex.
sentences.chinese: 阿索卡擡頭，發現自己正望着雷克斯上尉。

sentences.english: You want me to rescue captain thrace ?
sentences.chinese: 你想讓我去營救色雷斯上尉？

sentences.english: The Voyage of Captain Woodes Rogers, round the world.
sentences.chinese: 上尉的伍茲羅傑斯環球航行。

sentences.english: Captain Mayes was amazed by the amount of time and effort put into building the set.
sentences.chinese: 梅耶斯上尉對佈景所花費的時間和精力感到不可思議。

sentences.english: Captain Jones raised his gun and bang, another Indian bit the dust.
sentences.chinese: 瓊斯上尉舉起槍開了火，又一個印軍被擊斃了。

sentences.english: The captain applied to headquarters for a transfer.
sentences.chinese: 上尉向司令部請求調動。

sentences.english: "He knows what people want and just rolls with it, " says Lieut.
sentences.chinese: “他知道人們想要什麼，只是用它卷，”上尉說。

sentences.english: The captain brought the men to attention as the general arrived.
sentences.chinese: 將軍到達時，上尉命令戰士們立正。

sentences.english: The captain billeted his soldiers on Mrs. Mary.
sentences.chinese: 上尉分派士兵住在瑪麗太太家。

sentences.english: Flight LiuChangLing fell in love with QingBaoChu mid-team leader of the MaXin blue captain.
sentences.chinese: 飛行中隊長劉長嶺愛上了情報處的馬昕藍上尉。

sentences.english: The captain posted guards at the door.
A captain commands a company or battery.
sentences.chinese: 一個上尉指揮一個連隊或炮兵連。

sentences.english: It has come from a direct descendant of Captain Gunter.
sentences.chinese: 它是來自鋼特上尉嫡系子孫。

definition: junior ranking officer in Chinese army/major/lieutenant commander
middle ranking officer in Chinese army/lieutenant colonel/commander
high ranking officer in Chinese army/colonel
senior official/senior officer/commanding officer/CL:位[wei4]/sir (term of address for senior officer)
lowest-ranked noncommissioned officer (e.g. corporal in the army or petty officer, third class in the navy)
